added.title: The Scoop
added.description: The Titans find it odd when Starfire becomes friends with an ice cream scoop.

added.title: Chicken in the Cradle
added.description: Beast Boy neglects his responsibilities, leaving the other Titans to raise his baby chick.

added.title: Kabooms Part 1
added.description: The Titans are excited to see the movie version of their favorite show "Babies vs Dogs".

added.title: Kabooms Part 2
added.description: Inspired by the "Babies vs Dogs" movie, the Titans decide to make a big Hollywood film of their own.

added.title: Tower Renovation
added.description: Following the destruction of their Tower by Slade, the Titans go house hunting.

added.title: My Name Is Jose
added.description: The Titans have Raven give them new super powers but have a hard time adjusting.

added.title: The Power of Shrimps
added.description: Aqualad uses shrimps and prime rib to win back Raven.

added.title: Monster Squad!
added.description: The Titans want to be the scariest trick-or-treaters in town, so Raven casts a spell to turn them into real monsters.

added.title: The Real Orangins!
added.description: Robin tries again to tell the real origin story of the Teen Titans.

added.title: Quantum Fun
added.description: Robin takes the other Titans on a trip through the dizzying world of quantum physics.

added.title: BBRBDAY
added.description: When he isn't invited to Beast Boy's birthday party, Robin throws his own party, with special guest Bob Uecker.

added.title: Slapping Butts and Celebrating for No Reason
added.description: When the Big Game is threatened the Titans must infiltrate the football stadium and stop the attack.

added.title: Nostalgia Is Not a Substitute for an Actual Story
added.description: The Titans time travel back to the 1980s to determine whether or not it was the best decade ever.

added.title: Business Ethics Wink Wink
added.description: Starfire dreams of becoming a successful business alien princess and joins a cookie-selling organization to learn the proper skills.

added.title: The Colossus
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that it isn't wise to upset Hector, Elmore's resident Giant.

added.title: The Knights
added.description: Gumball and Tobias compete for Penny's affection by putting on the lamest duel in history.

added.title: The Fridge
added.description: When Mom discovers Gumball has no ambition she is determined to turn him into a winner.

added.title: The Flower
added.description: When Gumball sees Leslie with Penny, he is overcome with uncontrollable jealousy.

added.title: The Banana
added.description: Darwin lends his pen to Banana Joe but, when it comes back chewed, Gumball's thoughts turn to revenge.

added.title: The Job
added.description: Dad gets his first job as a pizza delivery guy, which rocks the very fabric of the universe.

added.title: The Remote
added.description: The Wattersons' battle for possession of the TV remote gets dirty.

added.title: Halloween
added.description: Carrie takes Gumball, Darwin and Anais to a real haunted house party on Halloween!

added.title: The Treasure
added.description: Anais uncovers a secret that she's convinced will lead her to the Watterson's hidden family treasure.

added.title: The Skull
added.description: Gumball and Darwin make friends with classmate Clayton, a compulsive liar who can shape-change!

added.title: The Bet
added.description: When Bobert becomes Gumball's servant for a week, Gumball realizes robots obey everyone's command... even if that means destroying you!

added.title: The Watch
added.description: Gumball and Darwin learn that getting a family heirloom back off an old man is harder than you might think.

added.title: The Bumpkin
added.description: Envious of his rustic lifestyle, Gumball invites Idaho over to teach the Wattersons how to live like a potato.

added.title: The Phone
added.description: When Gumball and Darwin get their first cell phone, they foolishly give out their number to super-intense Ocho.

added.title: Christmas
added.description: Santa Claus is coming to town. Unfortunately he gets run over by the Wattersons, so it's up to them to save Christmas.

added.title: Itch to Explore
added.description: Craig's quest to map the entire Creek takes him and his friends into the treacherous Poison Ivy Grove.

added.title: You're It
added.description: A vicious game of tag wreaks havoc on the Creek, claiming Kelsey as the next it.

added.title: Jessica Goes to the Creek
added.description: When Craig and Jessica are locked out of the house, Craig has no choice but to bring his little sister to the Creek.

added.title: The Final Book
added.description: The last book of Kelsey's favorite fantasy series goes missing from the library, so Craig decides to help her solve the mystery of who took it.

added.title: Too Many Treasures
added.description: Hoping to fix their fort, Craig enlists the 10 Speeds to give them a ride to the legendary Junk Pile.

added.title: Wildernessa
added.description: An encounter with Wildernessa, guardian of the wilderness, inspires Kelsey to take up a cause.

added.title: Sunday Clothes
added.description: JP dirties his last clean clothes and he must wear his Sunday best to the creek.

added.title: Escape from Family Dinner
added.description: There's a huge water balloon fight at the creek but Craig is stuck at home for a family dinner, unless he can escape.

added.title: Monster in the Garden
added.description: Craig is determined to catch the monster that has been wreaking havoc in Granddad's garden.

added.title: The Curse
added.description: Craig, Kelsey and JP run afoul of some no-good teenage witches and are cursed! Lousy teenagers!

added.title: Dog Decider
added.description: Unable to make tough decisions, Craig decides to put his choices in the hands of a dog named Fred.

added.title: Bring Out Your Beast
added.description: Craig wants to play a popular card game, so he decides to borrow Bernard's vintage and valuable cards.

added.title: Lost in the Sewer
added.description: Craig agrees to help The Sewer Queen map the sewers, but he quickly finds himself in over his head.

added.title: The Future is Cardboard
added.description: The kids meet an eccentric Cardboard Creator that invites Craig to help finish his masterpiece.

added.title: The Brood
added.description: Craig's determination to get his granddad a cicada shell causes him, Kelsey and JP to become trapped in their stump!

added.title: Our Stuff
added.description: After the bears play a little pickup basketball (they're very bad), they go back to grab their stuff by the side of the court only to find it's been stolen!  The Bears race across town trying to track down their stuff and end up cracking a giant case in the process.

added.title: Viral Video
added.description: The Bears think they have what it takes to make and star in a viral video, but when Nom-Nom decides that they don't, Grizz breaks into the koala's limo in an effort to change his mind.

added.title: Food Truck
added.description: The Bears open up a food truck after being disappointed by the food options available to them. In an effort to drum up business, they start selling their food to animals until the animals go a little crazy.

added.title: Chloe
added.description: Chloe spends time with the Bears in an effort to research them for an upcoming presentation. But when the Bears sneak a peek at her very dry report, the Bears decide to jazz it up with exaggerated facts about themselves and their lifestyle.

added.title: Panda's Date
added.description: When a vendor at the Farmer's Market (LUCY) sticks Panda with an EpiPen reviving him after an allergic reaction, Panda comes to in the arms of his dream girl. Panda tries to woo this woman of his dreams but his brothers and his own insecurities get in the way.

added.title: Everyday Bears
added.description: It's a normal day for the Bears. This means that Ice gets in a fight with a Roomba, Panda's life gets turned upside down when a mouse invades his room and Grizz gets stuck in a tree. You know, everyday stuff for a bear.

added.title: Burrito
added.description: Grizz likes Burritos. A lot. So much so that after a restaurant makes a Bear-Sized Burrito, Grizz can't bring himself to eat such a majestic work of art. He carries the burrito everywhere making it a new and increasingly smelly part of his life.

added.title: Primal
added.description: Have the Bears lost their survival instincts by living in the modern world? Grizz wants to know so he purposefully gets the Bears lost in the deep forest.

added.title: Jean Jacket
added.description: The Bears find a bedazzled jean jacket in a dumpster. It's just about the coolest thing they've ever seen and seems to make the wearer of the jacket extremely lucky. But after the Bears fight over who gets control of the jacket, they have to consider that their denim blessing has become a curse.

added.title: Nom Nom
added.description: When Nom Nom shows up on the Bears' doorstep, disheveled and deposed from his spot as cutest internet star ever after a recent meltdown, he enlists the Bears to help him regain his title.

added.title: Shush Ninjas
added.description: The Bears are fed up with the decay of etiquette at today's theaters. The Bears take it upon themselves to be the police of the theater, sneaking up like ninjas to shush people who ruin the movie for others with their bad manners.

added.title: My Clique
added.description: Chloe, a child prodigy, finds it difficult to connect with her much older classmates. The Bears take her under their wing and show her how to make great college friends.

added.title: Charlie
added.description: You know that one annoying friend who just can't get the hint? That's Charlie, and he's Bigfoot. The Bears meet him when Charlie signs up on a home-sharing website to spend a weekend with the Bears. Charlie is the worst possible house guest for the Bears and nearly destroys their house.

added.title: Brother Up
added.description: After Panda stumbles and accidentally scares a pack of wolves away in the process, the hierarchy of the Bears is disrupted. Suddenly, Panda has become the alpha bear, and he and Grizz have to deal with the consequences of an emotional Panda being the leader of the three Bears.

added.title: Occupy Bears
added.description: When the city plans to destroy the Bears' cave in order to make way for a new cell phone tower, Grizz and Panda must find evidence from their past that proves they have rights to their land. And in case that fails, Ice Bear protests and tries to sabotage the construction crew.

added.title: Monstra-City/Shut the Pup Up
added.description: Monstra-city: When all the monsters move from Monster Isle to Townsville, it's up to the Girls to keep the peace./Shut the Pup Up: When the Talking Dog witnesses a crime, he moves in with the girls for protection. But the girls soon realize this chatterbox dog is less than the perfect pet.

added.title: Toast of the Town/Divide and Conquer
added.description: Toast of the Town: When the Mayor rubs Chemical X on his head for hair growth, all of him grows and stomps through Townsville./Divide and Conquer: When the Amoeba Boys learn how to divide, they multiply wreaking havoc as the many amoebas descend upon Townsville.

added.title: Save Mojo/Substitute Creature
added.description: Save Mojo: An animal activist group sets out to protect Mojo, ensuring that he can behave like the naturally evil monkey that he is./Substitute Creature: A substitute teacher comes to Pokey Oaks and the girls are sure that this creature teacher is up to no good.

added.title: The Boys Are Back in Town
added.description: Him brings the Rowdyruff Boys back, protecting them from the girls' feminine wiles.

added.title: Pee Pee G's/Boy Toys
added.description: The Pee Pee G's: When the girls wake up to discover their bed is wet, none of them want to admit that they are the guilty party./Boy Toys: The girls allow Princess to become a Powerpuff Girl when they realize they need help trying to defeat the Rowdyruff Boys.

added.title: Burglar Alarmed/Shotgun Wedding
added.description: Burglar Alarmed: A new burglar comes to Townsville and his first robbery is at the house of the Powerpuff Girls?/Shotgun Wedding: The Professor tries to find out what a Lumkins really is.

added.title: Lying Around the House/Bubble Boy
added.description: Lying Around The House: The girls tell little white lies that turn into a big, bad problem./Bubble Boy: Realizing that the only way to beat the Rowdyruff Boys is to join them, Bubbles takes Boomer's place in this rough-and-tumble band of boys.

added.title: Seed No Evil/City of Clipsville
added.description: Seed No Evil: When a prehistoric caveman thaws out in Townsville, the girls must stop him from stealing the Mayor's seeds./City of Clipsville: The girls reminisce on their adventures in these new, never-before-seen clips!

added.title: Keen on Keane/Not So Awesome Blossom
added.description: Keen on Keane: It's Valentine's Day and the girls notice that Ms. Keane is all alone. Time for a little matchmaking, but who will be the lucky fella?/Not So Awesome Blossom: When Blossom's attack plans fail one after the other, she loses confidence in herself as the group's leader.

added.title: Power-Noia
added.description: The girls have become paralyzed by their greatest fears. Who could be behind such an evil trick?

added.title: The Last Donnycorn
added.description: When Donny the Unicorn is hunted by a seemingly unstoppable foe, the Powerpuff Girls have to find a way to save him before it's too late!

added.title: Green Wing
added.description: When volunteering at a retirement home, Buttercup meets an old woman who claims she used to be a superhero.

added.title: 15 Minutes of Fame
added.description: When Bubbles' video goes viral, she goes to great lengths to maintain her status as a big-time director.

added.title: Splitsville
added.description: The girls learn to appreciate each others's style after having to each fight solo.

added.title: Clawdad
added.description: While visiting the lake, Buttercup vows to capture a legendary uncatchable crawdad.

added.title: Super Sweet 6
added.description: Morbucks throws the biggest birthday party of all time, and Blossom is the only one not invited.

added.title: A Star is Blossom
added.description: When Bubbles gets the lead in the school play, Blossom's jealousy consumes her.

added.title: Mini Golf Madness
added.description: Buttercup takes her game winning mini golf ball, in spite of ominous warnings of dire consequences.

added.title: Summer Bummer
added.description: When the beach is taken over by the most excellent Bro Sharks, will the Girls be gnarly enough to save the day?

added.title: The Tell Tale Schedulebot
added.description: After Blossom and Buttercup break Schedulebot, they'll do anything to keep the truth from coming out.

added.title: Musclecup
added.description: Feeling inadequate as a superhero, Buttercup bulks up…to the max.

added.title: Take Your Kids to Dooms Day
added.description: The Girls spend the day with the Professor at his boring office, only to find that the office comes with a terrible secret.

added.title: The Bubbles-Sitters Club
added.description: Bubbles tries to prove that she's responsible enough to own a dog.

added.title: Buttercup vs. Math
added.description: When Buttercup tests into Honors Math, she tries to avoid being labeled a nerd.

added.title: Home, Sweet Homesick
added.description: When the Girls go to Camp, Blossom has a hard time leaving her schoolwork at home.

added.title: Stuck Together
added.description: Steven and Lars spend some time together.

added.title: The Trial
added.description: Steven goes on trial.

added.title: Off Colors
added.description: Steven finds some unusual new allies.

added.title: Lars' Head
added.description: Lars finally lets Steven in.

added.title: Dewey Wins
added.description: Steven helps Mayor Dewey run a difficult campaign.

added.title: Gemcation
added.description: Greg and the Gems take Steven on vacation to help him relax.

added.title: Raising the Barn
added.description: Pumpkin goes missing!

added.title: Back to the Kindergarten
added.description: Steven, Amethyst and Peridot try to spruce up the Kindergarten.

added.title: Sadie Killer
added.description: Steven and the Cool Kids start a band, but they have trouble finding their sound.

added.title: Kevin Party
added.description: Kevin is throwing a party, and Steven is invited.

added.title: Lars of the Stars
added.description: Lars rises to the occasion.

added.title: Jungle Moon
added.description: Stevonnie finds themself alone on an adventure.

added.title: Your Mother and Mine
added.description: Steven takes Garnet to meet some of his new friends.

added.title: The Big Show
added.description: Steven shoots a documentary that follows a local band as they get their first big break.

added.title: Pool Hopping
added.description: Garnet and Steven explore the most unlikely timelines in Beach City.

added.title: A Very Special Episode
added.description: Rainbow Quartz 2.0 promised to hang out with Onion the same day Sunstone scheduled a home safety Geminar! How can Steven be in two places, and two fusions, at once?

added.title: Snow Day
added.description: Steven and the Crystal Gems get a chance to catch up when they're all snowed in together.

added.title: Why So Blue?
added.description: Steven has heard rumors of a pair of Gems that are still destroying worlds. If he can't stop them, maybe Lapis can.

added.title: Little Graduation
added.description: Steven and the Gems celebrate Little Homeschool's first graduating class.

added.title: Prickly Pair
added.description: After leaving Little Homeschool, Steven has found a new hobby, plants.

added.title: In Dreams
added.description: Steven's dreams start broadcasting onto his bedroom TV.

added.title: Bismuth Casual
added.description: Pearl invites Bismuth to the roller rink for a lesson on how to forge human relationships.

added.title: Together Forever
added.description: Connie has a really clear vision for her future. Steven wants to make sure he'll be a part of it.

added.title: Growing Pains
added.description: Steven visits a doctor for the first time.

added.title: Mr. Universe
added.description: Greg takes Steven on the road to find the origins of the Universe name.

added.title: Fragments
added.description: Steven heads to the woods to train with a powerful mentor.

added.title: Homeworld Bound
added.description: Steven heads to the Diamonds for advice on how to control his new powers.

added.title: Everything's Fine
added.description: Steven insists that everything is fine.

added.title: I Am My Monster
added.description: Everything is not fine.

added.title: The Future
added.description: Steven is finally ready to move on.

added.title: Slumber Party Panic
added.description: Finn must keep his promise to Princess Bubblegum and cover up the zombie problem they've created.

added.title: Trouble in Lumpy Space
added.description: Finn and Jake must travel to a far-off land to stop Jake from becoming permanently Lumpy.

added.title: Prisoners of Love
added.description: The boys try to cool off but get trapped by the Ice King.

added.title: Ricardio the Heart Guy
added.description: Finn becomes jealous of Princes Bubblegum's new suitor.

added.title: Enchiridion
added.description: Finn quests for a book that will make him a better hero.

added.title: The Jiggler
added.description: Finn and Jake must figure out what's wrong with a creature.

added.title: Tree Trunks
added.description: Finn and Jake try to go on a quest while protecting Tree Trunks.

added.title: Business Time
added.description: Finn and Jake must take charge after the businessmen they've outsourced some of their work to go too far.

added.title: My Two Favorite People
added.description: Jake tries to broker peace between Rainicorn and Finn.

added.title: Memories of Boom Boom Mountain
added.description: Finn gets caught up in trying to make everyone happy.

added.title: Dungeon
added.description: Finn tries to conquer a dungeon without Jake's help.

added.title: Rainy Day Daydream
added.description: Jake's imagination runs wild and Finn has to stop it before it kills them.

added.title: Henchman
added.description: While trying to rescue a helpless stranger, Finn becomes Marceline's slave.

added.title: What Have You Done?
added.description: Finn and Jake befriend the Ice King in an attempt to save the ice cream people.

added.title: Gut Grinder
added.description: Finn and Jake chase a mysterious villain who's been stealing gold from helpless villages.

added.title: Starter Pack
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to stop Muscle Man from messing with Thomas.

added.title: Wallpaper Man
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby are driving to a Halloween party and tell scary stories to pass the time.

added.title: Pie Contest
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to prove to Benson that they can be judges at the pie contest.

added.title: 150-Piece Kit
added.description: Benson wants to prove that he performed a famous drum solo.

added.title: Bald Spot
added.description: Muscle Man wants to hide his bald spot at all costs.

added.title: Guy's Night
added.description: Pops wants to beat the milk challenge to prove he's one of the guys.

added.title: One Pull Up
added.description: Rigby needs to do one pull-up so he can pass the park physical.

added.title: The Longest Weekend
added.description: Muscle Man has to make it through a week without contacting Starla.

added.title: Sandwich of Death
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby have to find a cure for the Death Sandwich before Benson dies.

added.title: Ace Balthazar Lives
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby want to reunite the lead guitarist of Adrenaline with his band.

added.title: Do or Diaper
added.description: Mordecai has to kiss Margaret by the end of the week or else wear a diaper.

added.title: Quips
added.description: Skips has to tell his cousin Tips to stop telling bad jokes.

added.title: The Power
added.description: Mordecai & Rigby find a mysterious keyboard that allows them to do anything they want, including accidently sending Benson to the moon.

added.title: Just Set Up the Chairs
added.description: Mordecai and Rigby get distracted while setting up chairs for a kids birthday party and unleash a monster that terrorizes the entire park.

added.title: Rigby's Body
added.description: After Rigby eats an excessive amount of junk food, his body quits on him, leaving him a ghost-like consciousness. Mordecai and Skips must find his body before the day is over.

added.title: The Interrogation
added.description: After Mr. Reese discovers his precious car smeared with meatball sauce, he pulls out his officer's cap and enlists Clarence to help his investigation to nab the culprit.

added.title: Lost Playground
added.description: When Aberdale Elementary's beloved playground equipment is replaced with safe, boring alternatives, Clarence and the gang seek out their old playground equipment in the legendary lost playground yard.

added.title: Bird Boy Man
added.description: Sumo discovers an injured roadrunner, names him Hot Sauce, and nurses him back to health. The two become inseparable pals, but Sumo learns that a wild animal can't be contained.

added.title: Freedom Cactus
added.description: Clarence draws a comic for the school paper and it becomes a huge hit with the kids. When angry parents step in and censor the comic's crass humor, Clarence must stand up for his artistic vision.

added.title: Plane Excited
added.description: Clarence is all excited visit his grandma when he learns that Chad has never been on a plane. Clarence makes it his mission to help Chad get through a hectic flight.

added.title: Escape from Beyond the Cosmic
added.description: When Clarence accidentally breaks a local arcade game Jeff has become obsessed with, Clarence puts together his own real-life version of the game at home, encouraging Jeff to act out his fantasy in levels created exclusively by Clarence.

added.title: Ren Faire
added.description: Clarence and his pals venture to the Aberdale Renaissance Faire. Clarence confuses a medieval play for reality, and vows to stop the evil black knight from getting the princess.

added.title: Time Crimes
added.description: When Clarence is convinced he has the power to manipulate time he vows to only use his abilities for good. However, a day at school puts his morals to the test when he's given the ultimate choice to help his friends or pause time in the name of fun.

added.title: Saturday School
added.description: After creating an unapproved mural on a wall at Aberdale Elementary, Clarence, Jeff and Sumo are forced to come to school on a Saturday to clean up as punishment.

added.title: Attack the Block Party
added.description: Clarence, Jeff and Sumo investigate a high school party down the street, which they mistake for an alien invasion.

added.title: Field Trippin'
added.description: After a pit stop bathroom break during a school field trip, Clarence returns to the parking lot and accidentally gets on the wrong school bus - which takes him to a different school!

added.title: Ice Cream Hunt
added.description: Clarence enlists the help of his eccentric neighbor Larry to take the trio out for ice cream and the ride of their lives!

added.title: Company Man
added.description: When Clarence loses the ball during a soccer game, he ends up following it into an office building, where he's mistaken for the boss's kid and given free reign to wander around. Will he climb his way to the top of the corporate ladder or end up on the chopping block?

added.title: Stump Brothers
added.description: After Clarence and Sumo cause a power outage in Sumo's family home, they're sent off in the hot desert with Sumo's older brother to retrieve a generator part. Will they survive the trek or will Sumo's sibling rivalry boil over?

added.title: The Tails of Mardrynia
added.description: After reading a book about a mystical animal society in class, Clarence is inspired to round up local animals and recreate an animal world of his own to cheer up his friend Percy. But will Percy take the game too far?

added.title: Doctor Visit
added.description: Uncle Grandpa hates going to the doctor but he's overdue for an important vaccination.

added.title: The Cake Mistake
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and Mr. Gus eat a cake meant for someone else.

added.title: Sheep Deprivation
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a kid who can't fall asleep.

added.title: Trash Cat
added.description: Uncle Grandpa helps a cat who's afraid to take baths.

added.title: Uncle Grandpa's Odd-yssey
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang must retrieve Tiger from the pound before she's adopted out.

added.title: Surprise Party
added.description: Mr. Gus and Belly Bag are throwing a surprise party for Pizza Steve, as long as  Uncle Grandpa doesn't spoil their surprise.

added.title: Pizza Steve's Past
added.description: Uncle Grandpa and the gang learn of Pizza Steve's past stint in the food service industry. Pizza Steve wasn't always the Pizza Steve they know and love.

added.title: Belly Bros
added.description: When a kid is bummed that his favorite shirt won't fit over his big belly, it's up to Uncle Grandpa to show him that t-shirts come and go, but having a big belly is always cool.

added.title: Tiger Trails
added.description: In the final moments of helping a kid, Uncle Grandpa just needs his trusty Giant Realistic Flying Tiger, but when he finds out she's gone, it sends UG on a journey to find the tiger and figure out why she left.

added.title: Space Emperor
added.description: When UG mistakes a kid in a costume for an evil space emperor, he sends him to another dimension where he becomes an actual evil space emperor and UG must figure out some way to bring him home.

added.title: Funny Face
added.description: When Uncle Grandpa accidentally unleashes a floating Funny Face that's so funny you laugh yourself to insanity, the guys realize that only Gus' seriousness can save them, but will he help them after they've hurt his feelings?

added.title: Moustache Cream
added.description: When UG and the gang are in a rush to purchase some emergency moustache cream, they face a formidable foe: Mart Mart.

added.title: Drawing Time
added.description: When the tv goes out, Jessica and her friends make up their own story to entertain themselves.

added.title: Jessica's Picnic
added.description: Jessica and Nicole set out to have a fun picnic but run into challenges when everything goes wrong.

added.title: The Secret Invention
added.description: Jessica finds out Craig is working on a Secret Invention and sets out to help him with it.

added.title: Big Kid Bike
added.description: Jessica wants to learn to ride a big kid bike.

added.title: Rain Rescue
added.description: Jessica rescues her toys from the backyard as rain approaches.

added.title: Bedtime Routine
added.description: Jessica wants to be a big kid and get ready for bed all on her own, but she can't remember everything in her routine.

added.title: Small Uncle's Big Bath
added.description: When Jessica discovers her favorite toy is dirty she volunteers to give him a bath.

added.title: The Big Kid Playground
added.description: Jessica goes in the big kid part of the playground for the first time, and befriends Stanleigh.

added.title: Grocery Store Friend
added.description: While helping Duane at the supermarket, Jessica meets a new friend and has trouble staying focused on her responsibilities.

added.title: Glow Toy
added.description: When Jessica can't get a new toy to work, she learns a new way to appreciate it.

added.title: Jessica's Restaurant
added.description: Jessica opens a restaurant with her good friend Stanleigh, but will they be able to keep their customers happy?

added.title: Little Twin
added.description: When Jessica meets another kid at the park with an identical look as her, the two quickly form an unbreakable bond.

added.title: Spike the Hedgehog
added.description: When Jessica pet sits Stanleigh's hedgehog, she has to think on her feet.

added.title: Sleepover
added.description: Jessica has a sleepover at her grandparents' house and must survive the night without her plush toy, Small Uncle.

added.title: Family Photo
added.description: When the family has to dress up for a family photo, Jessica decides to express herself.

removed.title: Coffee Cave
removed.description: After finding out Ice Bear is a master barista, the Bears turn their cave into a popular coffee shop. But it all goes awry when Ice Bear gets too into coffee and goes berserk.

removed.title: The Goons
removed.description: Gumball sets out to win his Dad back by winning a blindfolded "dumb" race.

removed.title: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever/Just Desserts
removed.description: The Powerpuff Girls Best Rainy Day Adventure Ever: It's raining in Townsville and there is no crime or villainy afoot. So the girls must stay inside and come up with their very own Powerpuff adventure./Just Desserts: The Smith Family is back and they want revenge. Harold, Maryanne and the kids become a super villain team and make it their goal to destroy the perfect Powerpuff family.

removed.title: A Very Special Blossom/Daylight Savings
removed.description: A Very Special Blossom: When the Professor wants an expensive gift for Father's Day, Blossom makes the mistake of taking what she can't afford instead of giving him a gift from the heart./Daylight Savings: The Powerpuff Girls are exhausted in school from saving Townsville past their bedtime. What will happen to their town when the girls are put on a curfew?

removed.title: Mr. Gus Moves Out
